@kwestin Traditional RF proximity unlocking systems, as used in many “push-to-start” auto systems are vulnerable to the same class of attacks.
If you don’t have to press a button in the remote, it’s vulnerable.
Same thing with RFID (e.g. HID branded building access cards) systems, btw.
